http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/2000-to-receive-degrees-at-KLU-convocation/article14015541.ece

As many as 2,000 students who completed Ph.D, M. Tech, B. Tech, MCA, MBA, BBA and B. Com courses during 2014-15 from Koneru Lakshmaiah University (KLU) will be conferred with degrees during the fifth convocation of the university on January 23 (Saturday).The convocation will be organised in the open air theatre on the university campus in Vaddeswaram village of Guntur district at 4. p.m. on Saturday. Supreme Court Judge N.V. Ramana, who will participate as the chief guest at the function, will deliver the convocation address.KLU will confer honorary degree of D.Sc on Scientific Advisor to Raksha Mantri G. Satish Reddy.Cash awardsGold and silver medals and cash awards will be presented to toppers in different streams.KLU Chancellor M. Ramamoorty, Koneru Lakshmaiah Education Foundation president Koneru Satyanarayana, vice-presidents K. Raja Hareen and Haveesh Babu, KLU Vice-Chancellor L.S.S. Reddy, Pro Vice-Chancellor A.V.S. Prasad and Registrar T. Umamaheswara Rao will be among those who will attend the function.